 was beaten by Jannik Sinner at the Australian Open back in January, with the 22-year-old proceeding to lift the trophy.Djokovic was then forced to pull out of the French Open due to injury and, though he fared well at Wimbledon, he wascrushed by Carlos Alcaraz in the final of that prestigious competitionearlier this month.Novak Djokovic has opened up ahead of the Paris Olympics|PAGiven his age, some feel the 24-time Grand Slam winner is approaching the end of his glittering career.Yet Djokovic, speaking ahead of the Olympics, has now made it clear he has no plans to walk away from the sport just yet.\", \"from\": 414, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 431, \"end\": 444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jannik Sinner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jannik_Sinner\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999999410736127, \"rank\": 5.8926392672086445e-08, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 907, \"end\": 915, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.9999999410736127, \"rank\": 5.8926392672086445e-08, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not have the retirement clause in my mind to be honest even though I know a lot of people would love me to retire so that this era is done,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But I think as long as one of us is left in the competition, I think the era is still going.\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"JUST IN:Emma Raducanu fans vent fury as Andy Murray confirms tennis retirement after Paris OlympicsDjokovic admits the next generation are starting to make their mark.Alcaraz has four majors to his name already, while Sinner showed he'd be a force for the future with his victory Down Under at the start of the year.Djokovic, when asked about the pair, added: \\\"Of course, there is this change of generation and you have Alcaraz and Sinner currently that are two best players in the world, deservedly.\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1281, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Raducanu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Raducanu\"}, {\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8533452503197173e-56, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\